{"build_type":"library","description":"Concise lens for syscall arguments: the inverse of fill_syscall_args. Reads the full invoke_kernel_syscall instruction's positional arg1..arg6 string fields and appends each present arg's variable name (as a JSON string) into args_out, so the concise sys form carries {\"args\":[name,...]} symmetric to the concise call-arg shape consumed by resolve_arg_to_var. Recursive over slot (start 1, limit 7); builds the key \"arg\"+slot the same way fill_syscall_args does (append_reversed_decimal). Reuses create_empty_string_buffer, append_byte_into_growable_byte_buffer, append_reversed_decimal, locate_named_member_inside_mapping, encode_textual_payload_document_value, append_element_extending_document_sequence.","module_name":"render-concise-invocation-syscalls-representation","package_name":"render-concise-invocation-syscalls-representation","function_definitions":{"render-concise-invocation-syscalls-representation":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"instr","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"args_out","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"slot","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"zero","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"one","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":1},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"seven","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":7},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"slot2","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"conditional_branch","condition_type":"numeric_compare","operator":"<","lhs":{"value":"slot"},"rhs":{"value":"seven"},"branch_on_success":[{"instruction_type":"function_invocation","invocation_name":"create-empty-string-buffer-sequenc